@page "/docs/scroll"

<PageTitle>Scroll — BlazorMotion</PageTitle>

<div class="breadcrumb">Docs / <span>Scroll</span></div>
<h1>Scroll</h1>
<p>BlazorMotion provides the <code>ScrollTracker</code> service to read scroll progress and drive scroll-linked animations.</p>

<h2>Register and inject</h2>
<pre><code>// Program.cs — already included in AddBlazorMotion()
builder.Services.AddBlazorMotion();

// Component
@@inject ScrollTracker Scroll</code></pre>

<h2>Scroll progress</h2>
<p>Read the current scroll progress (0–1) of the page or a container element:</p>
<pre><code>@@inject ScrollTracker Scroll

&lt;Motion Tag="div"
        style="width: @@(Scroll.Progress * 100)%; height: 4px; background: #7c3aed" /&gt;

@@code {
    protected override async Task OnAfterRenderAsync(bool firstRender)
    {
        if (firstRender)
            await Scroll.TrackAsync(OnScrollUpdate);
    }

    void OnScrollUpdate(ScrollInfo info)
    {
        // info.Progress  → 0.0–1.0
        // info.ScrollY   → raw pixel offset
        StateHasChanged();
    }
}</code></pre>

<h2>ScrollInfo reference</h2>
<table class="prop-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td>ScrollX</td><td>double</td><td>Horizontal scroll offset in pixels.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>ScrollY</td><td>double</td><td>Vertical scroll offset in pixels.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Progress</td><td>double</td><td>Vertical scroll progress 0–1 (scrollY / maxScrollY).</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Scroll-linked scale</h2>
<p>Use scroll progress to drive any CSS value:</p>
<pre><code>void OnScroll(ScrollInfo info)
{
    _scale = 1 + info.Progress * 0.5;    // 1.0 → 1.5
    _opacity = 1 - info.Progress;        // 1.0 → 0.0
    StateHasChanged();
}</code></pre>

<div class="callout callout-tip">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> For triggering animations <em>when</em> an element enters the viewport (rather than scroll-linked), use <a href="/docs/in-view">WhileInView</a> instead.
</div>
